{title: Will The Angels Play Their Harps For Me}
{artist: Doyle Lawson}
{composer: Written by Walter Hirsch and Monte Wilhite}

[C]I was passing by a churchyard in the city
And I met a beggar [G7]old and [C]grey
With his hand outstretched he asked the folks for pity
And it made me sad to [G7]hear him [C]say
Oh I wonder (yes I wonder) will the angels (way up yonder)
Will the angels play their [G7]harps for [C]me
For my feet are (growing weary) and my heart is (growing dreary)
Will the angels play their [G7]harps for [C]me
Will I ride up to the pearly gates in glory
In a chariot of [G7]pure shining [C]gold
Will I see the folks that went up there before me
When I'm safely gathered [G7]in the [C]fold
Repeat #2
Oh a [F]many a mile I've travelled and a [C]million sights I've seen
I'm ready for the glory soon to [G7]be
For my [C]feet are (growing weary) and my heart is (growing dreary)
Will the angels play their [G7]harps for [C]me